NOTHING BETTER broke sharply then was guided out soon after while taking the lead, was headed from his inside by THAT'S RIGHT entering the turn, pressed that one around turn, moved to command in upper stretch then edged out to a clear advantage in mid stretch, kept on past the sixteenth marker, bumped when hooked by the winner and stayed gamely. COPPOLA , forced in a bit soon after the break, circled four wide into the lane and rallied mildly. ARTEMUS CITYLIMITS , in close and bumped at the break, was taken to rate inside, got out a few paths entering the turn, was guided back down past the three eighths, angled out for the drive and closed some. NOBLE EMOTION , forced in some after the break then was shuffled, regrouped and rated inside, worked outward for the drive and continued with effort. THAT'S RIGHT , bumped at the break, hustled up and bid inside a pair of foes to take command into the turn, took outside pressure around the turn, ceded the lead past the three sixteenths then weakened late. DETERMINED KINGDOM drifted out nearing the turn and failed to respond. BREAKTHROUGH came in after the break tightening some rivals, corrected and chased four wide, was carried out some nearing the turn, continued wide around the turn and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NAGIRROC , five wide outside rivals nearing the wire the first time, was deftly maneuvered towards the rail with six furlongs remaining, crept up to rate close just off the inside, worked through a seam leaving the three eighths and engaged the leader soon after, struck the top with a quarter to go, quickly kicked away after being shaken up in upper stretch, was kept alert with a right handed ask near the sixteenth pole then was steadily hand ridden to the wire. FUNTASTIC AGAIN took over inside rivals heading to the first turn, moved clear and set the pace towards the rail, ceded command to the winner nearing the lane but kept on with good effort through the final furlong to save the place. CIRCLING THE DRAIN broke a beat slow then was pinched back, regrouped and was taken to rate off the pace while saving ground, eased out and worked between rivals nearing the quarter pole, angled out in upper stretch, straightened and closed willingly. KINGFISH STEVENS , taken to rate off the pace and raced between runners past the half mile pole, made a two wide advance under asking into the stretch, shifted in a bit and kept trying to the wire. WONDERFUL JUSTICE (GB) settled off the rail, raced three deep near the half, angled five wide past the quarter pole but came up empty. MOONSTRIKE (GB) was steadied soon after the break, dropped off the pace, came three wide for the drive but lacked a rally. TOP RECRUIT , bumped at the start, was sent up to contest the early pace four deep, was brushed and carried out entering the first turn, regrouped to stalk three wide, raced four wide with pursuit past the five sixteenths then tired. FADETHENOISE , a bit fractious in the gate, vied two wide between runners then got a bit floating rivals into the first turn, got settled into the backstretch, stalked three wide, was joined from his inside by the winner leaving the three eighths, chased past the five sixteenths and faltered. A WESTERN YARN broke outward and bumped with TOP RECRUIT, straightened and disputed the issue three wide between foes passing the stands the first time, was carried out by FADETHENOISE into the first turn and brushed with his outer rival, regrouped to be a few lengths off the pace, moved up some off the rail past the half, shifted in to pursue around the final turn then gave way in the drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NATIONAL TREASURE made the early lead without coaxing, was kept well off the inner rail approaching the first turn, moved in entering the turn, set the pace slightly off the rail down the backstretch, eased out in upper stretch, was challenged by BLAZING SEVENS in upper stretch, dueled, was bumped near the sixteenth pole, dug in tenaciously and twice bumped with BLAZING SEVENS approaching the finish. BLAZING SEVENS , well wide entering the first turn, stalked the pace outside horses down the backstretch, took aim on the leader past the three eighths, bid for the lead outside NATIONAL TREASURE in upper stretch, dueled, bumped that one when drifting in near the sixteenth pole, finished gamely and twice bumped with NATIONAL TREASURE near the finish. MAGE , slightly off the inner rail on the first turn, rated between horses while stalking the pace down the backstretch, eased out four to five in upper stretch, drifted in briefly behind the top pair in mid stretch and finished evenly. RED ROUTE ONE , brushed by COFFEEWITHCHRIS leaving the starting gate, raced along the inner rail on the first turn, steadied when rank entering the backstretch, remained along the inner rail advancing near the five eighths, saved ground on the far turn, eased out in upper stretch and lacked the needed rally. CHASE THE CHAOS lacked speed, raced near the inner rail on the first turn, was off the rail down the backstretch, swung wide turning for home and passed tired horses. PERFORM lacked speed, raced outside horses down the backstretch, entered the stretch in the three path and weakened. COFFEEWITHCHRIS came out at the break, prompted the winner while snugly in hand down the backstretch, was under urging on the far turn and tired entering the stretch.
